    "Its advantages are significant: -OPT can substantially reduce tour length and improve solution quality; it is also easy to implement.",
    "However, its disadvantages include the exponential growth in the number of possible reconnection combinations as increases, leading to higher computational complexity.",
    "As mentioned in Section 3.2, 2-OPT has only one reconnection type, while 3-OPT has seven reconnection types.",
    "Additionally, -OPT may get trapped in local optima and cannot guarantee finding the global optimum.",
    "k k Using DL can not only identify which edges to remove but also select the most appropriate reconnection type from exponentially many possibilities."
